In development, React 18 mounts components, runs effects, **immediately cleans them up**, then runs effects again. Without the returned cleanup, the first effect's listeners are never removed before the second attachment—doubling listeners on every mount in dev. The cleanup function ensures proper teardown between the double-invocation, preventing accumulation even in Strict Mode.

The corrected code preserves identical external behavior: displays current `scrollY` and direction on scroll, logs on resize, and resets direction/position tracking correctly.
